org.safs.image

Class ReverseRectangle

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.awt.geom.RectangularShape
      • java.awt.geom.Rectangle2D
        • java.awt.Rectangle
          • org.safs.image.ReverseRectangle
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.awt.Shape, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable

    public class ReverseRectangle
extends java.awt.Rectangle
    ReverseRectangle functions as a standard Rectangle object. However, where a normal rectangle assumes 0,0 is at the top-left corner, this class assumes 0,0 is at the bottom-left corner.

    Consequently, rectangles with higher Y values are actually higher up on a plane than rectangles with lower Y values.

    The class primarily serves as a marker. Users must treat the Rectangle information accordingly when comparing or merging with other Rectangles.

    Author:
    Carl Nagle
